      <para id="id354321">Once again <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>A</m:mi><m:mi>i</m:mi></m:msub></m:math> and <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mi>i</m:mi></m:msub></m:math> are constant square matrices, and it is readily verified that
<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>X</m:mi><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>z</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> written as a product above is of the form</para>
