        <para id="id359324">Therefore we have proved the following Theorem:</para>
        <para id="id359330"><emphasis effect="bold">Theorem 53</emphasis><emphasis effect="italics"> <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mi>p</m:mi></m:msub><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>z</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> of order <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>K</m:mi></m:math> forms a unitary filter bank with linear-phase and PCS
filters iff there exists a unitary, order <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>K</m:mi></m:math>, <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mi>M</m:mi><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> matrix <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msubsup><m:mi>W</m:mi><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msubsup><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>z</m:mi><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>
such that</emphasis></para><equation id="uid301">
