    <section id="cid20">
      <title>Linear Phase Modulated Wavelet Tight Frames</title>
      <para id="id362958">Under what conditions do linear phase modulated filter banks
give rise to wavelet tight frames (WTFs)? To answer this question,
it is convenient to use a slightly different lattice parameterization than
that used for Class B modulated filter banks. A seemingly surprising result
is that some Class A unitary MFBs <emphasis effect="italics">cannot</emphasis> be associated with WTFs.
